Fitness or physical activity observations measure the patient's fitness indicators: resting heart rate, maximum heart rate, active time exercised, sedentary behaviour, sleep episodes, calories burned, distance reached or steps taken. Measures can be timed over arbitrary periods (sessions) or over a day or week.

title.value: Value Set Finnish PHR Vital Signs

description.value: This value set indicates the allowed vital sign result types in Finnish PRH. The concept Vitals signs panel (85353-1) is a grouping structure for a set of vital signs and includes related links (with type=has-member) to the Observations in this set (e.g. respiratory rate, heart rate, BP). The Blood pressure panel (85354-9) is used to group the component observations Systolic blood pressure (8480-6) and Diastolic blood pressure (8462-4).

title.value: Value Set Finnish PHR Fitness Results

description.value: This value set indicates the allowed fitness or physical activity result types in Finnish PHR. The concept Daily Activity fitness panel (62812-3) is a grouping structure for a set of physical activity, and for convenience also vital sign, measurements and includes related links (with type=has-member) to the Observations in this set or the parallel Finnish PHR Vital Signs value set (e.g. steps taken, minimum or maximum heart rate, calories burned, moderate to vigorous physical activity minutes, sedentary activity minutes, sleep episodes and exercises).
